cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.DC, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with constructing a plane spanner of a unit-disk graph using a localized algorithm, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The algorithm also involves communication between nodes, which suggests that it could be relevant to distributed computing, placing it in categories such as cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NE (Networks and Networking). The paper also presents an improvement over a previous algorithm, which could make it relevant to categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
